headline: Why the Dow Is Lagging Behind the S&P 500 and Nasdaq
summary: The Dow was moving in and out of positive territory on Monday because of struggles among its heavier hitters.  The blue-chip index rose more than 100 points shortly after the open but was essentially flat in the early afternoon.  The S&P 500 was up 0.3%, while the Nasdaq Composite was up 0.8%.
